President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden visited Joint Base Myer-Henderson Hall in Arlington, Virginia to celebrate the 75th anniversary of Toys for Tots. The President shared a personal story about his childhood stutter and thanked the organization for bringing joy to families across the country. He also expressed gratitude to the military members and their families in attendance, acknowledging the sacrifices they make during the holiday season. The President mentioned a young girl's story who received a gift from Toys for Tots when she immigrated to the United States, and how that experience inspired her to join the Marine Corps. Biden concluded his speech by encouraging the children in attendance to continue being brave and helping others.